title: PPPP’s Javed Iqbal wins PS- 37 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Javed Iqbal has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-37, Shaheed Banazirabad -2, by securing 70,383 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Inayat Ali Rind Independent Condidate, who bagged votes 20,492.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.62 %.
